, the student of literature, and the general reader to gain a more sensitive and immediate understanding of the form and spirit of Chrétien's poetry, and to appreciate the more Chrétien's great contribution to European literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aArthurian romances. 0aErec (Legendary character)vRomances. 0aErec (Legendary character)xRomances. 0aKnights and knighthoodvPoetry. 0aRomancesvTranslations into English. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  a1170.  aacademic.  aancient world.  aarthurian romance.  aceltic legend.  achivalry.  aclassic literature.  acoming of age.  acourage.  acourtly romance.  aeuropean literature.  afolklore.  afrench literature.  agender roles.  ajokes.  aking arthur.  aknight.  aknighthood.  aliterary history.  aliterary studies.  alove story.  alove.  amarriage.  amasculine.  amasculinity.  amedieval culture.  amedieval france.  amythology.  aold french.  apoetry.  apuns.  aquest.  ascholarly.  atranslation.  awomens roles.  aworld literature.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052091097340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520910973423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520910973/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles